## Musk clashes with neighbors in exclusive Austin suburb  

Elon Musk’s $6 million home in West Lake Hills, Texas, has sparked a dispute with neighbors after his team installed an unauthorized 16-foot chain-link fence, according to the New York Times. Despite his widespread popularity, residents in the upscale Austin suburb have expressed frustration over the construction.  

### Why It Matters  

This Musk neighbor dispute highlights the tension between high-profile figures and local communities, especially in affluent areas with strict zoning laws. The situation could set a precedent for how celebrity homeowners navigate neighborhood regulations—or risk alienating those around them. While Musk’s projects often draw attention, this clash underscores the importance of adhering to local ordinances to maintain community relations.
